questions.stem_text: A puppy and two cats together weigh 24 pounds. The puppy and the larger cat together weigh exactly twice as much as the smaller cat, and the puppy and the smaller cat together weigh exactly the same as the larger cat. How many pounds does the puppy weigh?
questions.answer_explanation: Let the weight of the puppy be P, the larger cat be L, and the smaller cat be S. We have the equations: P + L + S = 24, P + L = 2S, and P + S = L. Solving these equations gives P = 6.

Weight of the puppy and larger cat is twice the smaller cat
Weight of the puppy and smaller cat equals the larger cat
